17/08/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Several people were injured Sunday (August 16th) when some fans of the national league soccer team Vardar clashed with locals in Skopje. The fans threw stones at people and damaged several cars after their team suffered a 0-5 loss to Macedonia Gjorce Petrov. Police detained ten people for questioning. (Makfax, MIA, A1, Alsat, AP - 16/08/09)
